Background

		Mr. James E. Meyer, also known as Jim, has been the Chief Executive Officer of Sirius XM Holdings Inc. (also known as SIRIUS XM Radio Inc.) since December 18, 2012. Mr. Meyer served as the President of Operations and Sales at SIRIUS XM Radio from May 2004 to December 18, 2012. He served as a Consultant to SIRIUS and was responsible for overseeing and directing all operations and sales, including its automotive OEM business, retail markets, product management, strategic ... partners, engineering functions and geographical expansion. Prior to joining SIRIUS, Mr. Meyer served as President of Aegis Ventures, a general management consulting company. Before Aegis, he held a number of senior management position in consumer electronics including, Senior Executive Vice President, Digital Media Solutions of Thomson, a worldwide leader in consumer electronics. From January 1997 to December 2001, Mr. Meyer served as Senior Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of Thomson Consumer Electronics. He was responsible for Thomson's Digital Media Solutions Business Unit, a global business serving the entertainment, broadcast and content industries, including such clients as Disney, Warner Brothers, Dreamworks, Microsoft, Direct TV, ABC and BBC. He served as Special Advisor to the Chairman of Thomson Multimedia and also served as Thomson's Chief Operating Officer for the Americas and as Senior Vice President of Product Management, along with other senior management positions at General Electric and RCA during his 25 years in consumer electronics. He has been the Chairman of TiVo Corporation since July 7, 2015 and has been its Independent Director since 1997. Mr. Meyer has been a Director of StarSight Telecast Inc. since February 1996 and SIRIUS XM Radio Inc. since December 18, 2012. He serves as a Director of Rovi Guides, Inc. He serves as a Director of Escient Solutions and Progressive Gaming Inc. He has been a Director of Sirius XM Holdings Inc. since January 2013. He serves as Director of OpenGlobe located in Indianapolis, Indiana. He served as a member of the Supervisory Board of ENV nternational N.V. (formerly Equant NV), since February 19, 2003. served as director Technicolor SA. He served as Director of OpenGlobe Inc. He served as a Director of Progressive Gaming International Corporation (formerly Mikohn Gaming Corp.) from February 1999 to July 26, 2005. Mr. Meyer holds a B.S. in economics and an MBA from St. Bonaventure University.Read Full Background




